[~shaon] - the way I induced the problem while I was working on the issue was to push data up to the OSG and then delete it, on a loop. Here is a shell snippet I was using - 
{code:none}
while true; do \
s3curl.pl --id qa_1_102 --createBucket -- -s -vvvv http://objectstorage.d-32.autoqa.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com:8773/services/objectstorage/wesw-test; 
s3curl.pl --id qa_1_102 --put fake-lifecycle-with-transition.xml -- -s -vvvv http://objectstorage.d-32.autoqa.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com:8773/services/objectstorage/wesw-test/test-copy-source | xmllint --format - ; 
s3curl.pl --id qa_1_102 --delete -- -s -vvvv http://objectstorage.d-32.autoqa.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com:8773/services/objectstorage/wesw-test/test-copy-source ; 
s3curl.pl --id qa_1_102 --delete -- -s -vvvv http://objectstorage.d-32.autoqa.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com:8773/services/objectstorage/wesw-test ; 
done
{code}
The jobs for deleting buckets and objects wake up every 60 secs. and then perform the actual upstream and database work. So, by leaving this snippet run and trying to shutdown the cloud, I was able to get the shutdown to hang. After applying my fix, I did not see any crashes on shutdown related to Quartz and it never hung.
